detailedReviews.text: We had the chicken fettuccine and calzone and loved it.  The pasta was full of chicken and plenty for two.  The noodles tasted delicate and homemade, the sauce was light just right.  For the price I wasn't expecting it to be so amazing definitely the best deal in town.  My husband loved his calzone and the tiramisu was so fresh.  We have definitely found out go to Italian restaurant, our usual place raised there prices so we started looking around and found Napolis.

detailedReviews.author: L R
detailedReviews.text: Delicious pizza at a great price! Crust is on the crispy side, cheese is delicious. The additional discount for signing up for their text program makes an already great deal even better. Looking forward to coming back!

Excellent to-go pizza! As always!!
No dine-in, but wonderful pizza with fresh veggie ingredients. Highly recommend!
(Sidenote: We‚Äôve been eating Napoli‚Äôs food for YEARS, beginning in the early/mid-90s at what we think was their original location in Garland. As I recall, the founders were mom and pop who ran the place, and also their son whom we dubbed ‚ÄúFast Eddie‚Äù because he always moved around so quickly directing the kitchen to get food out fast and hot/fresh‚Ä¶he was a real character who always greeted us by name when we walked in as we were quite the regulars.

detailedReviews.author: Kevin Safstrom
detailedReviews.text: I work in the area so I've ordered several times.  I've had their pizza, which I love.  The crust is between a super thin napolitan style pizza and NY style - so it's perfect!  The sandwiches are amazing too.  I've had the the twisted sub, meatball sub and chicken parm sub, and all are great.  You can't go wrong with this place no matter what you order.  The staff are helpful and don't miss the details.  Just eat here.

detailedReviews.author: Monique Paul
detailedReviews.text: I have had pizza and chixken parm sandwich.   Sooo good.  Hits the spot!

detailedReviews.author: S R
detailedReviews.text: Napolis Pizza On The Go is truly a hidden gem! Their pizza is hands-down some of the best you'll find -perfectly crispy crust, fresh, high-quality toppings, and just the right balance of flavors. You can tell they put passion into every pie they make! On top of that, their service is outstanding friendly, fast, and always welcoming. This place is a must-hit if you're ever in McKinney. Whether you're a local or just passing through, do yourself a favor and grab a pizza. You won't be disappointed!

detailedReviews.author: Totally Buffs89
detailedReviews.text: I like to order my pizza with extra sauce.  I ordered the XL pizza recently and the extra sauce made the pizza a bit soggy.  They stretch the dough so thin it cannot handle the extra sauce.  It seems to me they use the same amount of dough for the L and XL but stretch it more in order to charge the XL prices.  The pizza tastes good but it is definitely not worth the price.

detailedReviews.author: Ryleigh Tyson
detailedReviews.text:
Ordered the chicken parm - I've had it from other Napoli locations many times, but this one was different. I'd like to start off by saying if you like a lot of spices/herbs, it's great. The chicken was wonderful, and my boyfriend really liked the pasta - so this is mostly my own experience.
Unfortunately, one bite of the pasta was overwhelming for me. There also seemed to be a spicy tinge as well that left my tongue numb - are there chili flakes in the sauce? I have a mild allergy to most peppers. I did not disclose this because the listing made no mention of spiciness and other locations didn't include it. I'll be sure to mention it next time to be safe.

The cheese was melted to perfection, and the tomato sauce was rich and flavorful. Steven‚Äôs attention to quality really shines through. For a quick and delicious meal, Napoli's is the place to go!

detailedReviews.author: Sumit Shrestha
detailedReviews.text: First of all the, ine of the best tasting pizza crust i have ever had on a pizza. I am one of those who doesnot like pizza crust but this place has different way of making their dough and it is absolutely amazing!! Also tried their wings and they were good. Prices were not that bad either. Secondly , great customer service and the gentleman helped us navigate through choices as it was my first time there. Definitely a place to try!!!

detailedReviews.author: John Sherry
detailedReviews.text: This is definitely my new favorite pizza and stromboli place! They do not skimp on the ingredients. And the crust is more flavorful than any other pizza I can recall. I would consider it a hidden gem. It is also priced very reasonably compared to other Italian pizza places I go to around me. You really should give them a go,  you won't be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Boa De Cocoa
detailedReviews.text: Pizza and pasta is always good. I am thoroughly disappointed with the Caesar salad.. $10.00 for a salad with literally ten pieces of lettuce and I was charged extra for dressing.. you guys have to do better about price gouging for salads.

detailedReviews.author: Bill O'Keefe
detailedReviews.text: The crust is great! The margherita may be the worst I've ever had. No fresh basil at all. Garlic oil that will keep vampires away for centuries and way too much cheese. The tomatoes were not roma, rather they were quartered slices of deli tomatoes. Obviously will never order that pizza again. The lasagna is good however, perfect for cool nights and red wine.

detailedReviews.author: Miky P
detailedReviews.text: They serve up more than just pizza, as I discovered during my recent visit. I tried the Tortellini Cheese with Alfredo sauce, and it was nothing short of delicious. The Alfredo sauce was creamy and well-seasoned, perfectly clinging to the generously stuffed tortellini. I was impressed with the portions, which were quite substantial, ensuring great value for the price. Given the quality of this dish, I'm definitely looking forward to returning soon to try more of their pasta offerings. A hidden gem for Italian cuisine lovers!

Good/decent for Dallas area pizza. My only criticism of the meat lovers is the sausage. It could have really used a good, high quality Italian Sausage in the mix. 4/5

detailedReviews.author: Josh Compton
detailedReviews.text: Yummy

detailedReviews.author: S L
detailedReviews.text: Sooo happy they added a Napoli‚Äôs pizza down the street from me! I have frequented the one in Allen and always loved it. detailedReviews.author: tisha Estep

detailedReviews.author: Robert Lewis
detailedReviews.text: We love getting takeout from Napoli‚Äôs.  The food and service is great! Definitely one of our favorite go to places in McKinney!  Fast and friendly service.

detailedReviews.author: Adam Vac
detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôm going to be perfectly honest‚Ä¶ first off, I‚Äôm from New Jersey (arguably the best pizza in the US) and while I stand behind the premise that even bad pizza is good‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm still critical of it. detailedReviews.text: We have had food from here twice now and both times the food was excellent! The XL pizzas truly are XL! The Ravioli, Lasagna, and Chicken Parm are all delicious! We will definitely continue ordering from here!
